		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Business logic</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Business logic</b> is a non-technical term generally used to describe the functional <a href="/wiki/Algorithm" title="Algorithm">algorithms</a> that handle <a href="/wiki/Information_exchange" title="Information exchange">information exchange</a> between a <a href="/wiki/Database" title="Database">database</a> and a <a href="/wiki/User_interface" title="User interface">user interface</a>. It is distinguished from input/output <a href="/wiki/Data_validation" title="Data validation">data validation</a> and product logic.</p>
